, 1915: 339, type locality: Gafsa, Tunisia, lectotype in MNHN [not examined].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D56B323B1369A9FB8F7BDD6A6290BE71" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">
<taxonomicName id="A209F7584D0FC3F9502795C32ED20616" authorityName="Chretien" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Galacticidae" genus="Galactica" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Galactica variinotella" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variinotella">Galactica variinotella</taxonomicName>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD3127059B7AA09154D7652FABCA177" author="Sattler, K" journalOrPublisher="In: Amsel HG, Gregor F, Reisser H (Eds) Microlepidoptera Palaearctica, zweiter Band, Teil 1" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" refId="B41" refString="Sattler, K, 1967. Ethmiidae. In: Amsel HG, Gregor F, Reisser H (Eds) Microlepidoptera Palaearctica, zweiter Band, Teil 1" title="Ethmiidae." year="1967">Sattler (1967</bibRefCitation>
: 140).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2B11C67E4BAC7819A4E562B1D8AA6E09" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="ECABEFD885DDA70CDB45F5933AF548E8" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="38AFD5565A3C937CF52C331F62842026" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">
The male lectotype was designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="FF14B6383FDDBA9E30230E8A6539AB5E" author="Sattler, K" journalOrPublisher="In: Amsel HG, Gregor F, Reisser H (Eds) Microlepidoptera Palaearctica, zweiter Band, Teil 1" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" refId="B41" refString="Sattler, K, 1967. Ethmiidae. In: Amsel HG, Gregor F, Reisser H (Eds) Microlepidoptera Palaearctica, zweiter Band, Teil 1" title="Ethmiidae." year="1967">Sattler (1967</bibRefCitation>
: 140) who transferred the species provisionally from the family 
<taxonomicName id="0F1C65CBB852C9E168E752A9BCAA5D19" authorityName="Busck" authorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Ethmiidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ethmiidae</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4488E14C10E161F2BFFDD72AF8188B77" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Galacticidae" genus="Galactica" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Galactica" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="126C03AF1BA537417397C2D3BD3CA7F1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">Galactica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The genitalia were unfortunately not examined and not illustrated. From the original description alone, the generic affiliation cannot be determined. The type is missing in the MNHN.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
